msgstr ""

#: ../../source/usage.rst:3 b9a4c3b45490418798dec906bd2cd796
msgid ""
"Here you can find detailed instructions on how to create and maintain an "
"ODKSM server instance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/usage.rst:5 7e9e54a56e7f4b0ab678a855fba6d3f1
msgid ""
"First of all you need to ensure the tool is correctly :doc:`installed "
"<installation>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/usage.rst:8 bdb1dd1a7b534819ab6dbd3e079c5557
msgid "Create a server instance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/usage.rst:9 260c531cd7fa4ea2b4bfc97868ef4e4a
msgid ""
"To create your first instance you will need to fill in the config file "
"``config.ini`` that can be found in the root directory of this tool."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/usage.rst:12 344deea8406b492da5e81b0a4f28e0f3
msgid ""
"We recommend to never modify files directly in the tool directory: it "
"will be easier to update the tool."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/usage.rst:14 3510f7289fee481cb919f93e40f08f9d
msgid ""
"Prepare a custom instance folder and copy the ``config.ini`` and "
"``ODKSM.bat`` files there, instead! You then need to edit ``ODKSM.bat`` "
"and set the variable ``ODKSM_FOLDER_PATH`` to the tool root folder."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/usage.rst:17 9abd910dfcac4b17aad40cf357816251
msgid ""
"The default_ ``config.ini`` is thoroughly documented and you can also "
"find all supported fields descriptions in the :doc:`config.ini "
"documentation <config>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/usage.rst:20 1b892c2ac2da4257acb8c448c2b42302
msgid ""
"Fields in the ``config`` and ``bat`` sections will be used to fill in "
"templates for the ``serverConfig.cfg`` (the file that will be passed with"
" the -config flag to the server) and ``run_server.bat`` (the bat that "
"will be used to launch the instance)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/usage.rst:24 905830d250794da784e6df3b6f8641cf
msgid ""
"Fields from the ``ODKSM`` section will be used directly by the tool to "
"set paths, mods and keys, amongst other things."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/usage.rst:26 b965a85a18ae4218ba0b814d1e1322cd
msgid ""
"You can specify user mods as a list in the config with the "
":option:`user_mods_list <ODKSM user_mods_list>` field or passing the path"
" of a mods preset file created by the Arma 3 Launcher with the "
":option:`user_mods_preset <ODKSM user_mods_preset>` field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/usage.rst:30 a78f13d4f07f49b8bdd05fb3f868b4d4
msgid ""
"Server side mods can be specified only as a list with the "
":option:`server_mods_list <ODKSM server_mods_list>` field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/usage.rst:32 d487c1e1372e4a54b901c1308d74a277
msgid ""
"Once you are satisfied with your config file, you may simply drag&drop it"
" on the ``ODKSM.bat`` to launch the tool."
msgstr ""

